###buttons theme

When generating the button theme, the system works from 2 [map scss](http://sass-lang.com/documentation/file.SASS_REFERENCE.html#maps), one acts generating properties of the default theme $button-default and $buttons generates the different variations, both map merge processing the result, you can pass as a `false` value if we want the element not to launch the default value

When working on a button and having states the mixon buton-active has been created that encapsulates the selectors of the state and launches the styles of the active map.

~~~scss
$button-default:(
  'base': (
    color: $white,
    border: 1px solid $gray-600,
    background-color: $gray-600
  ),
  'active': (
    background-color: darken($gray-600, 10%)
  )
);

$buttons:(
  'default': (),
  'primary': (
    'base': (
      border: false,
      background-color: $primary
    ),
    'active': (
      background-color: darken($primary, 10%)
    )
  )
);
~~~
